<doc id="68552" wikidata="Q2338482" url="?curid=68552" title="Abishua">
<text>Abishua ( &quot;ʾĂḇīšūaʿ&quot;, &quot;my father is rescue&quot;) was an early High priest of Israel.
Abishua is mentioned in the books 1 Chronicles (6:3-5) and Ezra (7:5) as the son of the High Priest Phinehas, son of Eleazar. As such, he is the great-grandson of Aaron, the brother of Moses and first High Priest. It is likely that Abishua was a contemporary of the Israelite judge Ehud and the Moabite king Eglon.

According to Josephus and other extrabiblical sources, he succeeded his father as High Priest (Antiquities 5.11.5; 8.1.3).

==Name and namesakes==
*The meaning of the name &quot;Abishua&quot; is uncertain, but may be &quot;the (divine) father is opulence.&quot;
*The name also appears in reference to a grandson of Benjamin in 1 Chronicles 8:4.

