<doc id="68614" wikidata="Q4695120" url="?curid=68614" title="Ahinadab">
<text>Ahinadab ( &quot;Ahinadav&quot;, &quot;my brother is noble&quot; or &quot;my brother has devoted himself&quot;), son of Iddo, is one of the twelve commissariat officers appointed by Solomon to districts of his kingdom to raise supplies by monthly rotation for his household. He was appointed to the district of Mahanaim (), east of Jordan.

